HTTP Requests and Responses:

*HTTP communications mainly consist of an HTTP request and an HTTP response. An HTTP request is made by the client (cURL/browser) and is processed by the server (web server). The request contain all of the details we require from the server including the resource (URL, path, parameters), any request data, headers or options we specify, and many other options. Once the server receives the HTTP request it processes it and responds by sending the HTTP response which contains the response code and may contain the resource data if the requester has access to it.


